1
00:00:14,867 --> 00:00:18,567
Are you obsessing about
her now after Amanda?

2
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:21,133
Amanda is trash compared to her.

3
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,267
Why even bring her up?

4
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,567
She's been gone
or a long time.

5
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:27,167
Rina was chasing me around until
I got out of the boutique.

6
00:00:27,233 --> 00:00:28,733
She was so desperate.

7
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:32,433
She really wanted to know
who Mrs. Madrigal was.

8
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,867
I have dreams for our baby too.

9
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:38,633
I want to hear her laugh.

10
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,800
Yen, I want to hear her cry.

11
00:00:40,867 --> 00:00:42,933
I want to teach her
how to play football.

12
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,633
But I wasn't able to do that

13
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:47,100
because I wasn't able
to save her.

14
00:00:47,167 --> 00:00:51,467
I lost their money
to a bad investment.

15
00:00:51,533 --> 00:00:55,300
You must think I'm really weak,
but I just got unlucky.

16
00:00:55,367 --> 00:00:56,267
And don't worry.

17
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:58,033
I won't run away
with your money.

18
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,733
I believe you.

19
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:00,833
Don't worry.

20
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:03,067
No one else will
know about this.

21
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:04,133
Thank you.

22
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:06,567
Money is everything to them.

23
00:01:06,633 --> 00:01:10,133
We're going to target
them financially.

24
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:12,333
To make sure they suffer.

25
00:01:13,133 --> 00:01:16,500
I think it's better to stay
this way for now.

26
00:01:16,567 --> 00:01:18,133
Give her some space.

27
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:20,200
Go out with your friends.
Have a few drinks.

28
00:01:20,267 --> 00:01:21,600
Have fun.

29
00:01:21,667 --> 00:01:23,233
You deserve it.

30
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:25,100
This is my last payment.

31
00:01:25,167 --> 00:01:26,200
Do you really think
I would fool you?

32
00:01:26,267 --> 00:01:27,900
And I want to get this
over and done with.

33
00:01:27,967 --> 00:01:31,200
That's how easy it is
to catch them with our bait.

34
00:01:31,267 --> 00:01:34,433
She will have all that money
in just a bit.

35
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:37,933
And I know where she's going
to spend it.

36
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:45,167
Good afternoon.

37
00:01:46,167 --> 00:01:47,100
- I am back.
- Good afternoon.

38
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:49,000
And as promised...

39
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,967
here is your cash.

40
00:01:53,033 --> 00:01:53,733
Thank you, Madame.

41
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:55,067
Thank you. So I guess...

42
00:01:59,867 --> 00:02:01,533
this is mine now.

43
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:04,133
Thank you very much.
Have a good day, ladies.

44
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,300
Thank you.

45
00:02:05,367 --> 00:02:07,400
- Hold it right there, Madame.
- Excuse me?

46
00:02:09,133 --> 00:02:09,700
Madame?

47
00:02:10,567 --> 00:02:11,067
Yes?

48
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:14,833
But we can't give you this item.

49
00:02:15,933 --> 00:02:17,900
I just paid you. That's my hat.

50
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:19,967
We can't let you have that,
Madame.

51
00:02:20,033 --> 00:02:22,100
Because you gave us
counterfeit money.

52
00:02:25,067 --> 00:02:26,767
What are you talking about?
That's impossible.

53
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:28,200
That's my hat! I paid you!

54
00:02:28,267 --> 00:02:29,333
Check that money.

55
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,333
I already did that.

56
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,433
Well, check it again!

57
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:33,833
All of them are fake.
It's counterfeit money.

58
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:35,600
It's impossible! This is my hat.

59
00:02:35,667 --> 00:02:36,500
I paid you.

60
00:02:36,567 --> 00:02:38,433
Perhaps you switched it up.

61
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:40,100
This is mine, okay?

62
00:02:40,167 --> 00:02:41,900
- Madame...
- I'm going. Excuse me.

63
00:02:41,967 --> 00:02:42,800
Excuse me.

64
00:02:42,867 --> 00:02:45,500
Please be careful
with your words.

65
00:02:45,567 --> 00:02:48,767
I'm still being respectful
because you're our patron.

66
00:02:48,867 --> 00:02:52,300
But we can report you for
using counterfeit money,

67
00:02:52,367 --> 00:02:54,800
and I can call the police.

68
00:02:54,867 --> 00:02:55,500
Security?

69
00:03:00,633 --> 00:03:03,833
I'm sure there's an explanation
for all of this.

70
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:06,867
We'll let this slide, Madame.

71
00:03:06,933 --> 00:03:09,267
Because you've been
a VIP in our store.

72
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:12,733
But from now on, you will
be banned from this store.

73
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:16,500
No, no! Don't!
Don't get your hands on me!

74
00:03:16,567 --> 00:03:17,267
- No!
- Sorry, Ma'am.

75
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:18,800
- No, no.
- You have to go.

76
00:03:18,867 --> 00:03:19,533
I will be back!

77
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,800
I said, don't touch me!

78
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,300
This way, please.

79
00:03:24,367 --> 00:03:26,600
I paid so much in this shop!

80
00:03:26,667 --> 00:03:29,867
You're making a big mistake!

81
00:03:29,933 --> 00:03:31,500
I don't need an escort.

82
00:03:31,567 --> 00:03:33,633
Don't touch me. Listen to me.

83
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:34,633
I paid for it.

84
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:37,267
That hat is mine!
I already paid.

85
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:39,633
You can't ban me
from this shop

86
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:42,133
- Please, Ma'am.
- because I'm a patron!

87
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,033
I don't know.

88
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,633
I think you switched up
my money!

89
00:03:45,567 --> 00:03:46,667
Mrs. Madrigal?

90
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:49,733
Are you still interested
in this hat?

91
00:03:50,567 --> 00:03:53,433
I paid with real money!
What happened?

92
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:59,400
I said, don't touch me!

93
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:00,000
No!
Just leave, Ma'am.

94
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:02,767
What are you doing?

95
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:05,133
What the heck are you doing?
I told you not to touch me!

96
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,167
Don't touch me!

97
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:09,167
Don't touch me!

98
00:04:10,433 --> 00:04:11,100
Get out of my way!

99
00:04:48,033 --> 00:04:48,833
What is that?

100
00:04:50,567 --> 00:04:52,333
Zandro, you're so stupid!

101
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:54,167
What is that?

102
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:58,467
That's fake!

103
00:04:58,533 --> 00:05:01,433
I couldn't check all of it.

104
00:05:01,533 --> 00:05:03,467
And this never happened
to us before.

105
00:05:03,533 --> 00:05:04,733
You're so stupid!

106
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:05,933
You didn't check the money!

107
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,700
Look at what happened!

108
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:10,367
Who paid that money?

109
00:05:10,433 --> 00:05:11,300
Go get him.
Go and make him pay.

110
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:16,667
Rina, I know Elmer.

111
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:18,400
He's not capable of doing this
by himself.

112
00:05:18,467 --> 00:05:20,067
He can't come up with
this plan on his own.

113
00:05:21,133 --> 00:05:25,033
Go back and get him,
make him pay.

114
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:28,400
If he's working with
someone else to fool us...

115
00:05:29,367 --> 00:05:30,933
find out who it is.

116
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:35,200
I will make him eat all
that counterfeit money.

117
00:05:37,767 --> 00:05:38,767
Where's the stuff you bought?

118
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:41,167
It's in the car.
Someone's bringing it here.

119
00:05:46,233 --> 00:05:48,233
I had so much fun.

120
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:49,533
I spent money,

121
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:52,600
but it was all worth seeing Rina
getting dragged by the guards.

122
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:56,233
She looked like a slave
outside the boutique.

123
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:57,600
She was so embarrassed.

124
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:03,400
I'm sure Rina is so anxious
right now.

125
00:06:04,033 --> 00:06:07,533
Because she doesn't know
who she's up against.

126
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,833
And I'm only getting started

127
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:12,000
because I will make her pay for
everything that she did to me.

128
00:06:12,067 --> 00:06:17,533
I will make her lose her mind
and make her wish she was dead.

129
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:35,500
Red!

130
00:06:36,300 --> 00:06:37,133
Red!

131
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,200
What's up?

132
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:45,133
- Hi, hello.
- Sab.

133
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:48,533
Are you good at
playing darts now?

134
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,233
You might lose again.

135
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:52,700
Is he serious?

136
00:06:52,767 --> 00:06:54,033
Well, he can.

137
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:58,967
Actually, we're just glad that
you're here after what happened.

138
00:07:06,967 --> 00:07:07,867
You know what?
Let's just have fun.

139
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:11,100
One round of drinks on me.

140
00:07:11,167 --> 00:07:12,067
That's what I'm talking about.

141
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:13,700
- Let's go. Let's drink.
- Shot! Let's go.

142
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:14,633
Okay.

143
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,367
Let's go.

144
00:07:34,433 --> 00:07:35,967
Yen, I'm sorry.

145
00:07:37,067 --> 00:07:39,267
I've been busy with work.

146
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:45,633
I didn't know you were going
through a hard time right now.

147
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:50,233
How's Red? What did he say?

148
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,800
What about his parents?

149
00:07:55,267 --> 00:07:56,367
Are they okay?

150
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,700
Red and I are not doing so well.

151
00:08:06,233 --> 00:08:06,967
Hold on.

152
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:09,767
If you two are not
doing so well...

153
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,900
then why don't you
just come home with me?

154
00:08:13,967 --> 00:08:17,567
No, Auntie. I was to blame.

155
00:08:18,433 --> 00:08:19,667
I was the one who's
been cold to him

156
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:21,600
because I can't move on yet.

157
00:08:21,700 --> 00:08:23,333
I'm still hurting.

158
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,300
And he seems okay.

159
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,767
I just can't do it.

160
00:08:37,967 --> 00:08:38,733
- For the win!
- There he goes.

161
00:08:40,167 --> 00:08:42,500
Hey!

162
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:43,167
You just got lucky.

163
00:08:44,033 --> 00:08:45,033
You need to practice more.

164
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:47,133
I think Sab is better than you.

165
00:08:49,033 --> 00:08:51,233
Let's get another shot.

166
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:52,467
Let's drink some more.
Let's drink.

167
00:08:52,533 --> 00:08:53,133
Okay, game.

168
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:56,600
I understand how you feel, Yen.

169
00:08:57,233 --> 00:09:03,000
But you and Red need to support
each other right now.

170
00:09:03,067 --> 00:09:06,433
Because both of you
lost a child.

171
00:09:07,733 --> 00:09:10,133
You need to help each other out.

172
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:16,433
If you were at fault...

173
00:09:18,833 --> 00:09:20,300
you should apologize to him.

174
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:26,000
Don't prolong it.

175
00:09:27,167 --> 00:09:28,600
Because you love him, right?

176
00:09:30,667 --> 00:09:32,567
You might lose him...

177
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:37,100
just like how we lost your mom.

178
00:09:44,967 --> 00:09:46,967
I can't bear it anymore, Auntie.

179
00:09:55,667 --> 00:09:56,333
Red?

180
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:58,700
Red?

181
00:09:59,167 --> 00:09:59,967
Where is he?

182
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:03,900
Emma?

183
00:10:04,967 --> 00:10:05,900
Have you seen Red?

184
00:10:07,633 --> 00:10:09,533
Why are you looking for my son?

185
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,667
So you can give him
a hard time again?

186
00:10:15,067 --> 00:10:16,133
I'm sorry, Auntie.

187
00:10:19,667 --> 00:10:21,833
He went out drinking
with his friends.

188
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:25,067
He'll be out late.

189
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:26,900
He didn't tell me
he was going out.

190
00:10:26,967 --> 00:10:28,067
Why would he do that?

191
00:10:28,133 --> 00:10:29,233
The two of you aren't
talking, remember?

192
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:30,700
You had a fight.

193
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:35,733
Red usually goes out
drinking with his friends

194
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:37,867
when he's in a bad mood.

195
00:10:37,933 --> 00:10:39,267
Didn't you know
that about him?

196
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:41,833
No.

197
00:10:43,233 --> 00:10:45,033
One, two, three, go!

198
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:45,667
Wait!
Cheers!

199
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,700
Wait, wait!

200
00:10:47,767 --> 00:10:49,233
Let's take a video first.

201
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:50,167
Come on.

202
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:51,267
Let's make this
night unforgettable.

203
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:53,233
- Sab, what are you doing?
- Let's go. Come on!

204
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:54,367
Put that away.

205
00:10:54,433 --> 00:10:57,767
I never thought I'd see
you like this again.

206
00:10:57,833 --> 00:11:01,467
It's good to see you're still
the life of the party.

207
00:11:01,533 --> 00:11:02,333
Yes!

208
00:11:03,133 --> 00:11:07,167
I thought you'd change
after what happened to Eden.

209
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:09,267
Why?

210
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:11,333
Nothing is changing.

211
00:11:13,033 --> 00:11:15,033
I'm happy right now
because I'm a free man.

212
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:15,633
You know what I mean?

213
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:19,167
No diapers to change.

214
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:21,200
I don't need to make milk.

215
00:11:22,533 --> 00:11:24,300
Because my baby's gone.

216
00:11:24,367 --> 00:11:25,867
What else can I do? Right?

217
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:28,233
Excuse me.

218
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:32,500
Let's drink! This is the life!

219
00:11:32,567 --> 00:11:35,300
The single life!
The bachelor life!

220
00:11:35,367 --> 00:11:36,433
My baby's gone.

221
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:39,033
My baby's gone.

222
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:50,733
Oh my God.

223
00:11:53,633 --> 00:11:56,967
So you still have a lot
to learn about my son.

224
00:11:58,900 --> 00:12:00,233
And yet you say...

225
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:01,800
you love him.

226
00:12:04,667 --> 00:12:09,533
Well you still don't know many
things about the person you said

227
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:10,333
you love.

228
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:18,933
Emma, I want a massage.

229
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:26,067
Yes!

230
00:12:32,667 --> 00:12:33,233
Red...

231
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,633
I'm really sorry
about your baby.

232
00:12:37,767 --> 00:12:38,300
That's it?

233
00:12:39,333 --> 00:12:41,300
You won't tell me I told you so?

234
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:45,100
You won't ask if I regret
choosing Yenyen over you?

235
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:48,333
Red, I'm not a monster.

236
00:12:48,433 --> 00:12:49,733
You lost your baby.

237
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:53,533
And I can't imagine how
painful it is for you.

238
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:56,467
And besides...

239
00:12:57,300 --> 00:13:00,533
I've long accepted that
you love Yenyen and not me.

240
00:13:01,533 --> 00:13:02,500
I've moved on.

241
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:04,267
Move on!

242
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:07,667
That's what Yenyen
and I argued about.

243
00:13:08,367 --> 00:13:09,500
I know she's hurting,

244
00:13:09,567 --> 00:13:12,933
and I've always been there
for her.

245
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,033
But I'm hurting too.

246
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:17,433
Who's there for me?

247
00:13:18,467 --> 00:13:19,567
Who's there for me?

248
00:13:23,467 --> 00:13:23,933
You know what?

249
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:28,333
I thought we'd go
through everything

250
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:30,733
as long as we're together.

251
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:32,900
Because that's what we
promised each other.

252
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:37,300
We promised each other
we would never be apart.

253
00:13:37,367 --> 00:13:38,800
That we'd always be together.

254
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:43,100
But she just pushes me away!

255
00:13:43,167 --> 00:13:44,533
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

256
00:13:46,133 --> 00:13:48,733
So now, I don't know what to do.

257
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:54,233
I lost my baby, and it feels
like I'm slowly losing her too.

258
00:14:02,767 --> 00:14:04,433
I'm sorry, Sab.

259
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:06,367
I don't know if you want
to hear all of this.

260
00:14:06,433 --> 00:14:07,300
I'm sorry.

261
00:14:07,367 --> 00:14:09,500
Red, don't worry. It's okay.

262
00:14:09,567 --> 00:14:10,767
You know what?

263
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:13,433
If there's more that you want
to say, tell me about it.

264
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,767
Let it all out.

265
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:16,567
I'll listen.

266
00:14:16,633 --> 00:14:20,633
And we were friends before
we started dating, right?

267
00:14:22,133 --> 00:14:23,833
And I miss having you
as a friend.

268
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:28,967
Really?

269
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:32,300
Will you still accept me...

270
00:14:34,033 --> 00:14:35,267
even though I'm now a bummer?

271
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:37,733
Even if I'm not the life
of the party anymore,

272
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,367
will you still hang out with me?

273
00:14:39,433 --> 00:14:42,367
Red, don't be silly. Come on.

274
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:46,900
As they say, if a person won't
stay with you at your lowest,

275
00:14:46,967 --> 00:14:49,633
then they don't deserve you
at your best.

276
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:52,967
Cheers?

277
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:57,667
Let's go.

278
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,233
Come on, drink some more.

279
00:15:03,633 --> 00:15:04,100
One more.

280
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:17,900
Cheers, Sab!

281
00:15:38,667 --> 00:15:41,867
Eden, just wait inside.
You might get rained on.

282
00:15:41,933 --> 00:15:43,667
It won't be good for you.

283
00:15:43,733 --> 00:15:45,633
I'll be fine.

284
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:47,567
I'll wait for Red.

285
00:15:47,633 --> 00:15:51,233
I want to talk to him.
I want to apologize.

286
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:52,333
If that's what you want.

287
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:04,200
Please help him, Sir.

288
00:16:07,367 --> 00:16:08,000
Yenyen...

289
00:16:11,967 --> 00:16:14,167
please, don't be mad at Red.

290
00:16:14,233 --> 00:16:16,367
He's going through
a lot right now.

291
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:19,600
He even told me that
you're pushing him away.

292
00:16:19,667 --> 00:16:21,033
Have pity on him.

293
00:16:21,967 --> 00:16:23,667
Sabina, please.

294
00:16:23,733 --> 00:16:26,367
Stop acting as if you care
about our relationship.

295
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:26,833
Hey.

296
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,000
You...

297
00:16:34,067 --> 00:16:34,967
stop.

298
00:16:37,567 --> 00:16:39,133
Don't give her a hard time.

299
00:16:42,233 --> 00:16:44,533
She's my friend.
She listens to me.

300
00:16:45,867 --> 00:16:47,967
Red, that's enough.
You're drunk.

301
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:50,000
You're right, Yenyen.

302
00:16:50,667 --> 00:16:52,600
Even though Red has told
me a lot about you,

303
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:55,500
I shouldn't say anything
about your relationship.

304
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:58,700
Here, take him.

305
00:17:01,867 --> 00:17:02,500
Go ahead.

306
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:05,433
I don't want to cause you
any trouble.

307
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:07,300
Good night, Red.

308
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,467
Hon, what's the matter?

309
00:17:36,300 --> 00:17:36,800
Nothing.

310
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:42,067
I didn't get to buy
the hat I wanted.

311
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:47,400
You're losing sleep over that?

312
00:17:52,767 --> 00:17:55,200
I want to sleep over there.

313
00:17:55,267 --> 00:17:55,733
Sit here!

314
00:18:01,233 --> 00:18:01,633
What now?

315
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,000
You're mad at me?

316
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:04,967
Why?

317
00:18:06,367 --> 00:18:09,300
I just talked to Sab.
We're just being friends.

318
00:18:10,233 --> 00:18:10,800
Friends?

319
00:18:11,633 --> 00:18:13,267
Is Sabina a good friend?

320
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:14,200
Have you forgotten what
she did on the island?

321
00:18:14,267 --> 00:18:15,933
That was a long time ago!

322
00:18:16,733 --> 00:18:18,000
Yen, that was a long time ago!

323
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:20,733
She'd moved on!

324
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:23,833
Something you're not
capable of doing!

325
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:28,933
Honestly, Yen, I feel better
when I'm with Sab.

326
00:18:29,933 --> 00:18:32,233
Because she talks to me.

327
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:34,267
She listens to me...

328
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:36,933
while you don't!

329
00:18:39,033 --> 00:18:42,133
I've tried to reach out to you
so many times.

330
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:43,933
I've made a lot of effort.

331
00:18:45,133 --> 00:18:48,133
But you just keep on pushing,
and pushing,

332
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:50,400
and pushing me away, Yenyen!

333
00:18:50,467 --> 00:18:51,967
Is that why you came to her?

334
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:55,300
Is that it, Red?

335
00:18:56,733 --> 00:18:58,333
Do you have to go
back to your ex?

336
00:18:59,233 --> 00:19:01,267
Would you run to her?

337
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:02,400
What else can I do?

338
00:19:03,933 --> 00:19:05,367
What else can I do, Yen?

339
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:08,233
She was there when I needed
someone to talk to.

340
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,033
And you weren't there.
What do you want me to do?

341
00:19:14,667 --> 00:19:15,667
Wait a minute.

342
00:19:18,033 --> 00:19:22,833
So how's your business
deal with Mr. Madrigal?

343
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:24,433
Are we going to make
money off of it?

344
00:19:26,933 --> 00:19:28,067
I'll just wait?

345
00:19:28,133 --> 00:19:30,367
You want me to wait around
until you talk to me?

346
00:19:30,467 --> 00:19:31,733
Because that's what
you've been doing!

347
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:34,100
Don't you realize
she has a motive?

348
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:35,433
- That's why she listens to you!
- That's Red.

349
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:38,300
- You're getting jealous again!
- They're fighting again.

350
00:19:40,367 --> 00:19:42,200
Come on, come on, come on.

351
00:19:42,267 --> 00:19:44,400
You're always getting jealous!

352
00:19:44,467 --> 00:19:45,633
That was a long time ago!

353
00:19:46,533 --> 00:19:50,633
I'm not getting jealous, Red.
I just don't trust Sabina!

354
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:53,067
Hey! Hey, what's going on here?

355
00:19:53,133 --> 00:19:55,633
Will you two just stop it?

356
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:56,667
That's enough.

357
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:01,233
Red, are you drunk?

358
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:07,067
You cannot resolve anything
if one of you is drunk.

359
00:20:07,133 --> 00:20:11,867
This is what happens when
you rush into things.

360
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:17,300
You don't know each other
that well yet.

361
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:21,667
But you got pregnant,
so what else can we do?

362
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:25,100
The two of you don't have
a good foundation

363
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:26,200
for your relationship.

364
00:20:26,267 --> 00:20:26,967
Rina.

365
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:32,933
Somebody has to speak
the truth here.

366
00:20:33,867 --> 00:20:36,633
The two of you are together
because of the baby, right?

367
00:20:37,433 --> 00:20:39,100
And now that the baby's gone.

368
00:20:39,167 --> 00:20:39,633
What are you going to do now?

369
00:20:41,267 --> 00:20:45,433
Maybe it's time for you guys
to rethink your relationship.

370
00:20:46,567 --> 00:20:47,433
I think...

371
00:20:48,667 --> 00:20:49,900
both of you are not happy
in your relationship anymore.

372
00:20:58,033 --> 00:20:58,933
Red?

373
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,000
- Red, Red.
- Red, Red.

374
00:21:01,067 --> 00:21:01,933
Are you okay?

375
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,033
Red!

376
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:03,633
Red.

377
00:21:04,433 --> 00:21:04,900
Red.

378
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:10,100
Eden, just go into your room.

379
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,300
We'll take care of him.

380
00:21:50,733 --> 00:21:52,767
It's only a matter of time,
Eden.

381
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:55,433
And you'll come back to me.

382
00:21:59,333 --> 00:21:59,767
Yen?

383
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:03,400
Yen?

384
00:22:06,933 --> 00:22:08,400
Yen, let's talk.

385
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:12,567
We're having lunch.
Come and have lunch with us.

386
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:15,467
Yen?

387
00:22:20,867 --> 00:22:21,433
Red?

388
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,067
Let her be.

389
00:22:28,667 --> 00:22:31,533
If she doesn't want to join us,
just leave her alone.

390
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:36,500
But I can't leave her.

391
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:43,233
Maybe she needs space for now.

392
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:44,400
Maybe some other time?

393
00:22:46,467 --> 00:22:48,567
Why don't you join us?

394
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:51,700
It's been a while
since we ate out.

395
00:22:51,767 --> 00:22:53,067
You, me, and your dad.

396
00:22:54,933 --> 00:22:56,067
Join us for lunch.

397
00:22:56,133 --> 00:22:57,500
Do it for Mom?

398
00:23:11,900 --> 00:23:13,400
- Table for two.
- Hi, Ma'am. Hi, Sir.

399
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:13,933
This way, please.

400
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,367
Oh yes, al fresco.

401
00:23:17,333 --> 00:23:17,900
Thank you.

402
00:23:17,967 --> 00:23:19,033
Thank you, Sweetheart.

403
00:23:19,833 --> 00:23:20,667
Thank you.

404
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:24,767
Here's the menu.

405
00:23:24,833 --> 00:23:26,000
Thank you.

406
00:23:26,067 --> 00:23:27,267
Thank you.

407
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:28,200
Are you hungry?
Yes.

408
00:23:32,367 --> 00:23:36,100
I really don't feel comfortable
going out without Eden and Red.

409
00:23:36,933 --> 00:23:40,033
It seems like we left
our problems at home.

410
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:42,833
What do you want to do?
Bring them here?

411
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:44,400
What for?
So they can fight here?

412
00:23:45,067 --> 00:23:47,367
I've had enough already.
It's just too much.

413
00:23:47,433 --> 00:23:49,100
They're too...

414
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,067
what's the word for it?

415
00:23:52,133 --> 00:23:52,833
Toxic?

416
00:23:52,900 --> 00:23:55,467
Toxic. Exactly. It's too toxic.

417
00:23:55,567 --> 00:23:56,633
You're right.

418
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:58,833
Can you check on Mrs. Madrigal?

419
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:00,067
She might want to
order something.

420
00:24:01,300 --> 00:24:03,100
Wait, is it the client
in the VIP room?

421
00:24:05,167 --> 00:24:05,967
Excuse me?

422
00:24:06,833 --> 00:24:08,467
Did you say Mrs. Madrigal?

423
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:10,800
Is she here?

424
00:24:10,867 --> 00:24:12,733
Sorry, Ma'am. Do you know her?

425
00:24:13,467 --> 00:24:15,933
We're close friends.
Mrs. Madrigal and I.

426
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,767
Is she here? Where?

427
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:18,700
Rina.

428
00:24:18,767 --> 00:24:21,967
She's in VIP Room 1.

429
00:24:22,033 --> 00:24:23,467
Okay. VIP Room 1.

430
00:24:23,533 --> 00:24:25,600
All right.
I'll quickly say hello.

431
00:24:25,667 --> 00:24:26,633
Okay, thank you.

432
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:31,100
Don't do it, Rina.

433
00:24:31,167 --> 00:24:33,200
She might be in an important
business meeting.

434
00:24:33,267 --> 00:24:34,833
I don't want you to interrupt.

435
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:37,400
I won't let this opportunity go.

436
00:24:37,467 --> 00:24:39,367
I just want to, you know,
meet her,

437
00:24:39,433 --> 00:24:41,967
say hello, introduce myself,
right?

438
00:24:42,033 --> 00:24:43,167
I'm excited.

439
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:52,867
Mrs. Madrigal?

440
00:24:52,933 --> 00:24:54,133
Mrs. Madrigal.

441
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:57,267
Mrs. Madrigal, hello?

442
00:24:57,333 --> 00:24:59,167
This is Rina Ramos.

443
00:25:01,633 --> 00:25:04,367
I know that you two
really love each other.

444
00:25:05,133 --> 00:25:07,267
That would be unfair
to your baby.

445
00:25:07,333 --> 00:25:10,633
She was created because
you love each other.

446
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:12,000
Red is sincerely
in love with you.

447
00:25:12,067 --> 00:25:15,300
I can't imagine what you two
are going through.

448
00:25:15,367 --> 00:25:18,833
But don't doubt the love
you have for each other.

449
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:22,200
Do you have an enemy
who could do this to us?

450
00:25:22,267 --> 00:25:24,400
You know me,
I get along with everyone.

451
00:25:24,467 --> 00:25:27,767
If the sender hates me,
then why did she call you?

452
00:25:27,833 --> 00:25:31,800
I can only think of one person
who can do this.

453
00:25:31,867 --> 00:25:33,667
Someone who keeps sending us
all kinds of things.

454
00:25:33,733 --> 00:25:35,000
It's Miss Amanda.

455
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:36,767
You know, you're right, Red.

456
00:25:36,833 --> 00:25:39,233
Yen, I tried to respect
your mom.

457
00:25:39,300 --> 00:25:41,633
But if she won't leave us alone,
I will forget she's your mom.

458
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:43,000
I might end up hurting her.

459
00:25:43,067 --> 00:25:46,100
Red, don't talk like that.
You're not that kind of person.

460
00:25:46,167 --> 00:25:48,767
But she's forcing me
to be this likes!

461
00:25:48,833 --> 00:25:51,133
Yen, we lost our baby
because of her.

462
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:53,033
And now she's targeting my mom!

463
00:25:53,833 --> 00:25:55,300
When is she going to stop?
